---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Aetna International in Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-aetna', text: 'Why Aetna for Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Who It\'s Best For', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Colombia', href: '/countries/colombia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Aetna International Review', href: '/providers/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Aetna vs GeoBlue', href: '/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 35)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Pioneer', coverage: 'Core inpatient', price: '$130-170/mo' },
  { plan: 'Voyager', coverage: 'Inpatient + outpatient', price: '$170-220/mo' },
  { plan: 'Navigator', coverage: 'Comprehensive', price: '$220-280/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Aetna International Health Insurance in Colombia"
  description="Guide to Aetna International health insurance for expats in Colombia. Strong US-backed coverage with global reach."
  headline="Aetna International in Colombia"
  subheadline="US-backed international coverage with strong network and CVS Health resources. Good choice for American expats in Colombia."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/colombia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Aetna Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Aetna International in Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International, backed by CVS Health, brings significant resources and a strong network to international health insurance. For American expats in Colombia who want coverage from a familiar US brand, Aetna provides continuity and reliability.
  </p>
  <p>
    With comprehensive plan options and integration with CVS Health's broader healthcare ecosystem, Aetna offers a robust option for Colombia's expat community.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$170-280</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Age 35)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">CVS Health</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Backed by major US insurer</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">US Coverage</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Strong US network access</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Aetna Colombia Quote"
    description="US-backed coverage for American expats in Colombia."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-aetna">Why Aetna for Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International works well for certain Colombia expats:
  </p>

  <h3>US Brand Familiarity</h3>
  <p>
    For Americans, Aetna is a known quantity. If you've had Aetna coverage before, the experience—claims process, member portal, customer service approach—will feel familiar.
  </p>

  <h3>CVS Health Integration</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to CVS Health resources when in the US</li>
    <li>MinuteClinic visits covered</li>
    <li>Pharmacy integration for prescriptions</li>
    <li>Digital health tools and telehealth</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Strong US Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    If you frequently return to the US or might need US-based care, Aetna's domestic network is extensive. This matters for:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Family visits back to the US</li>
    <li>Seeking specialized care in US facilities</li>
    <li>Eventually returning to the US</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Colombia Hospital Network</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bogotá:</strong> Access to major private hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>Medellín:</strong> Coverage at leading facilities</li>
    <li><strong>Direct billing:</strong> Available at network hospitals</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
    Prices shown for healthy 35-year-old. Actual premiums depend on age, health history, selected coverage, and deductible.
  </p>

  <h3>Cost Factors</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Age:</strong> Main driver of premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Plan level:</strong> Pioneer vs Navigator makes significant difference</li>
    <li><strong>Deductible:</strong> Higher deductibles reduce premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage area:</strong> Americas vs worldwide</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>What's Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital stays, surgery, ICU</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, specialists (Voyager+)</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Worldwide emergency coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation to appropriate facility</li>
    <li><strong>Prescription drugs:</strong> Covered with plan benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Wellness:</strong> Preventive care benefits</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions: Underwriting or exclusion periods</li>
    <li>Maternity: Waiting periods apply</li>
    <li>Mental health: Coverage varies by plan</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Who It's Best For</h2>

  <h3>American Expats</h3>
  <p>
    US citizens who want coverage from a familiar American insurer with strong US network access when visiting home. The CVS Health backing provides resources that other international insurers can't match in the US.
  </p>

  <h3>Corporate Expats</h3>
  <p>
    If your employer offers Aetna International, it's a solid choice. The administrative integration with US-based employers tends to be smooth.
  </p>

  <h3>Frequent US Visitors</h3>
  <p>
    If you return to the US often—for family, business, or preferred medical care—Aetna's domestic network is a significant advantage.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Visa Compliance</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      Aetna International meets Colombia's digital nomad visa insurance requirements. Your policy documents serve as proof of coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Aetna Plans for Colombia"
    description="Find the right US-backed coverage for your needs."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage details are estimates based on typical scenarios. Get a personalized quote for accurate pricing based on your age, health, and coverage needs.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
